problem_statement:
Warnings for using '.' in dataset name.
## Description
Since I upgraded to kedro 1.0.0 from 0.19.12 I get a lot of warning messages for using '.' in my dataset names.

## Context
My first pipeline only has a 2 level namespace so I can create a dataset for each of the coverage.model variants. The second pipeline uses a 3 level namespace so that I can apply separate coverage level filters as defined in my parameters and save each individual dataset accordingly. If i change the '.' to  '_' in the catalog (e.g. {product}.{sponsor}.{coverage}_{model}_policies_filtered), the second pipeline will not be able to find this dataset in the catalog. 

Originally I had the dataset defined as "{product}.{sponsor}.{coverage}.{model}.policies_filtered" in kedro 0.19.12

Is there a better way to implement this or will I have to disable the warning messages?

## Steps to Reproduce
Pipeline 1:
```      
for product, sponsors in settings.DYNAMIC_PIPELINE_MAPPING.items():
        for sponsor, coverages in sponsors.items():
            for coverage, models in coverages.items():
                for model in models:
                    _pipeline.append(
                        pipeline(
                            nodes=[
                                Node(
                                    func=rename_columns,
                                    inputs=[
                                        f"{coverage}.{model}_policies_dtype",
                                        "params:policy_rename_cols",
                                    ],
                                    outputs=f"{coverage}.{model}_policies_renamed",
                                ),
                                Node(
                                    func=process_policy_func,
                                    inputs=[f"{coverage}.{model}_policies_renamed"],
                                    outputs=f"{coverage}.{model}_policies_cleaned",
                                ),
                                Node(
                                    func=filter_df,
                                    inputs=[
                                        f"{coverage}.{model}_policies_cleaned",
                                        f"params:{coverage}.{model}.policy_filter",
                                    ],
                                    outputs=f"{coverage}.{model}_policies_filtered",
                                ),
                            ],
                            namespace=f"{product}.{sponsor}",
                            tags=[coverage, model],
                        )
                    )

    return sum(_pipeline)
```     


